data.text:
WYCN (channel 44) is an independent television station licensed to Kannapolis, North Carolina, United States, serving the Charlotte area. Owned and operated by the Central Networks Corporation division alongside Charlotte-licensed Central owned-and-operated station WBZ-TV (channel 15), both stations share studios on North Tryon and West 23rd streets north of uptown Charlotte, while WYCN's transmitter is located near Reedy Creek Park in the Newell section of the city.

ATSC 3.0 lighthouse service[]

On June 29, 2021, WYCN converted the digital channel 19 to ATSC 3.0, hosting simulcasts from WNC-TV, WCHE, WBZ-TV, WUCE and WCTU. Existing ATSC 1.0 channels from WYCN previously on channel 19 are hosted by WCHE, WBZ, WUCE and WCTU, but retain their virtual channel 44 identities as part of the arrangement.

The station's digital signal on channel 19 is multiplexed:
